      <description>Beyond just reading data from files, we can also create our own files and write data directly to them.
Opening a File for Writing In Python, we&amp;rsquo;ll use the .open() method we&amp;rsquo;ve been using to read from a file to also open a file for writing. So, here&amp;rsquo;s an example of what that might look like:
import sys from pathlib import Path import io class Writer: @classmethod def main(cls, args): if len(args) &amp;gt; 1: path = Path(args[1]) try: with path.</description>
